    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n# Problem description\n\nI'm trying to scroll horizontally with a keymap in all modes.\n\nWhen using vim.keymap.set, <C-o>zh and <C-o>zl do not work in visual mode, despite the fact that <C-o>zh and <C-o>zl being input from my keyboard in visual mode working fine, and the fact that the keymap is being set correctly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n## Relevant configuration to reproduce the problem\n```\nvim.keymap.set({'i', 'v'}, '<S-ScrollWheelUp>', '<C-o>zh')\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<S-ScrollWheelUp>', 'zh')\n\nvim.keymap.set({'i', 'v'}, '<S-ScrollWheelDown>', '<C-o>zl')\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<S-ScrollWheelDown>', 'zl')\n```\n\n## Steps to reproduce the problem\n1. In a document with text, try <C-o>zh in visual mode\n2. Observe that this works\n3. With the configuration in a document with text, try Shift + Scroll wheel in visual mode\n4. Observe that this does not work\n5. Observe that steps 1 and 3 work in normal and insert mode.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nScrolling is possible with a keymap in visual mode.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot sure how to configure a vimscript config to test this\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 44\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide 0.16.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNot sure\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom Fedora package repository",
